history.content:
BERKE1337’S BACK!!

BERKE1337, the renowned cybersecurity club, is finally back! We are currently building up a cyber community here at UC Berkeley to compete in CTFs (computer security competitions), learn from each other, and interact with the overarching security community from industry to academia. Our top priority as a club is to be all inclusive and have fun learning through different club activities!

BERKE1337 Introduction/Weekly Meetings:

We will be giving an introduction to what we do, who we are, objectives, and a look into the field of cybersecurity. Come one and come all, invite anyone you think may be interested in participating!

Monday 3/7 from 6-7 @ SOCS 175 (Social Sciences Building, Barrows Hall) or https://berkeley.zoom.us/j/97383944720

Join our Discord server:

Get all our upcoming events, announcements, and general chatter at https://discord.gg/hfXDEtZKCQ

Join our mailing list:

If you haven't yet, please fill out the form at https://forms.gle/r2rrvrUqoaZDmLiF8 to get put onto our mailing list and so we have a better understanding of our member!

We hope to see you next week, let’s all code on together!

Conner Mi

BERKE1337 Executive Officer
